reviews.review: Love the closure to an amazing series.  I laughed, I cried, it was better than Cats.
Amazing and definitely beats expectations of the movie!
Loved the graphics. Movie was very entertaining.
Felt a bit rushed at times, but the movie delivers. It makes good use of the traditional Star Wars characters and plots, while adding new twists and a satisfying ending.
I thought it was not bad but really lacked depth in comparison with the other recent Star Wars movies.

Like the Game of Thrones final season, it was an ending that complete killed my desire to go back and revisit what came before.  I wanted to love it, the first time I saw it I was completely locked in trying to not miss anything...and its just not a movie that rewards you for paying attention.

Could almost feel the screenwriters trying to please the fans, as opposed to telling a compelling story.  It tried to have emotional moments without actually following through on any real tragedy.  The return of an old supposedly-dead villain was...pointless and unexplained.  The twists were the same - running back to the safety of old ideas without adding any new fresh emotional context.

Just a complete mess, and singlehandedly took the Star Wars franchise off of the "Must See in Theaters" list for me until further notice.

The family and I watch this final of the original episodes.  We really enjoyed how the story did not seem to leave too many loose ends.  I am sure as I watch the episodes in the proper order along with the side movies, we will see more and have more questions.  And I cannot wait for the experience.
Thought it was very well done. If you like Star Wars movies, you will like this one. We enjoyed it.

JJ sacrificed the integrity of the trilogy and this film to dish up a bunch of fan service in a terribly paced movie with unmotivated characters, no stakes, and a half-baked villain that distracts from  a tremendous cast and stunning VFX. Ben and Rey shine through the mess though.
Epic but failed In places like the whole sith congregation derivative of Harry Potter Billy Dee was GAGA RICHARD E Grant always a delight
